summary.text:
EventAdmin component for managing events and questions.
Allows administrators to add, open, close, display, hide, and delete questions.
It also provides functionality to pick and hide individual free-text answers.

Handles GET requests to retrieve all invite codes.
Requires user authentication. Only authenticated users can view invite codes.

content.text: A JSON response with a list of invite codes or an error.

summary.text: The incoming request object.

Handles POST requests to create a new invite code.
Requires user authentication. Only authenticated users can create invite codes.

content.text: A JSON response with the created invite code or an error.

summary.text: The incoming request object containing invite code details.

EventPage component for audience members to view and answer questions for a specific event.
It fetches event and question data, manages user sessions, and handles answer submissions.

PresenterPage component for displaying real-time question results to an audience.
It fetches event and question data, and updates results via Socket.IO.
A form component for administrators to add new questions to an event.

InviteCodeManager component provides an interface for administrators to manage invite codes.
It allows adding new invite codes and viewing existing ones.
A component that animates a number change with a simple count-up/down effect.

content.text: The rendered component displaying the animated number.

summary.text: The component props.

value.text: The target value to animate to.
